<docbook><section><title>WhenDoINeedTheProgressNativeClient</title><para> </para><bridgehead class="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml:h2">When do I need the Progress native client?</bridgehead>
<itemizedlist mark="bullet" spacing="compact"><listitem> <emphasis>When using any Single-Tier data access driver for Progress,</emphasis> the Progress native client must be installed on the same machine as the Single-Tier driver.</listitem>
</itemizedlist><itemizedlist mark="bullet" spacing="compact"><listitem> <emphasis>When using any Multi-Tier data access driver for SQL-89 connections to Progress, and the OpenLink Request Broker and Progress-specific Database Agent are not installed on the Progress server host,</emphasis> the Progress native client (Progress® Client Networking) must be installed on the same machine as the Broker and Agent.</listitem>
</itemizedlist><itemizedlist mark="bullet" spacing="compact"><listitem> <emphasis>When using any Multi-Tier data access driver for SQL-92 connections to Progress or OpenEdge,</emphasis> the Progress native client (Progress® Client Networking) must be installed on the same machine as the OpenLink Request Broker and Progress-specific Database Agent, <emphasis>including when this is also the Progress server host.</emphasis> </listitem>
</itemizedlist></section></docbook>